From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0027/N] oopStorage: use SafeFetch64 for active_index_safe under CHERI

`OopStorage::Block::active_index_safe` reads an 8-byte `size_t`
field atomically via `SafeFetchN((intptr_t*)&_active_index, 0)`.
It static-asserts `sizeof(intptr_t) == sizeof(_active_index)`, which
holds on every 64-bit platform — until CHERI/Morello purecap, where
`intptr_t` is `__intcap` (16 bytes) but `size_t` is `unsigned long`
(8 bytes). The assert fires, and even if relaxed `SafeFetchN`'s
16-byte read would walk past the end of `_active_index`.

Use `SafeFetch64`/`int64_t*` under CHERI to read exactly 8 bytes.
Keep the original `SafeFetchN`/`intptr_t*` path for non-CHERI
where the type sizes still match by construction.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0027)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/oopStorage.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/oopStorage.cpp
@@ -299,8 +299,15 @@ void OopStorage::Block::set_active_index(size_t index) {
 }

 size_t OopStorage::Block::active_index_safe(const Block* block) {
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // CHERI: sizeof(intptr_t) is 16 (capability), but _active_index is a
+  // size_t (8 bytes). SafeFetchN would over-read; use SafeFetch64 directly.
+  STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(int64_t) == sizeof(block->_active_index));
+  return (size_t)SafeFetch64((int64_t*)&block->_active_index, 0);
+#else
   STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(intptr_t) == sizeof(block->_active_index));
   return SafeFetchN((intptr_t*)&block->_active_index, 0);
+#endif
 }

 unsigned OopStorage::Block::get_index(const oop* ptr) const {
